value.title: Biden names Obama-era UN ambassador Samantha Power to lead USAID
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden announced that former U.S. Ambassador to the United Nations Samantha Power will be his nominee for administrator of the United States Agency for International Development (USAID), a position that now will be added to the National Security Council.

value.title: Live updates: House moves to impeach Trump for 'incitement of insurrection' in Capitol riot
value.excerpt: The article of impeachment is expected to pass in the Democratic-controlled House, which would make Trump the first president in U.S.history to be impeached twice.

value.title: Trump administration nixes plans for controversial last-minute foreign trips to Europe and Taiwan
value.excerpt: Facing reported snubs by EU allies, Mike Pompeo's staying home, and Ambassador Kelly Craft won't visit Taiwan – a trip that would have infuriated China.

value.title: Hogan calls GOP delegate who attacked Pence a ‘Q-Anon conspiracy theorist’
value.excerpt: Larry Hogan (R) said Tuesday that a Republican state delegate who organized buses to the #stopthesteal rally in Washington — and called Vice President Pence a traitor during the breach of the Capitol — was a “Q-Anon conspiracy theorist.

value.title: Kamala Harris' Vogue cover defended by Anna Wintour amid controversy
value.excerpt: Vogue editor-in-chief Anna Wintour has spoken out after the magazine's cover shoot featuring Vice President-elect Kamala Harris received backlash.

value.title: Biden campaign bundlers to score senior White House positions
value.excerpt: At least eight top Biden campaign bundlers will be appointed or nominated to senior White House positions, according to a Fox News count.

value.title: Liz Cheney, No. 3 House Republican, to vote to impeach Trump
value.excerpt: Wyoming Republican Rep. Liz Cheney, the party's third-ranking House leader, announced on Tuesday that she will vote to impeach President Donald Trump, becoming the highest-ranking official from her party to support charging and removing him from office following the Trump-incited riot at the Capitol

value.title: Trump says 'I kept my promises' as he marks 450 miles of border wall, amid riot fallout in DC
value.excerpt: President Trump on Tuesday declared “I kept my promises” on his pledge to build a wall at the southern border, as he marked 450 miles of construction -- as he also tackled fallout from the riot at the Capitol last week.

value.title: Trump defends riot remarks as 'totally appropriate' before House vote on 25th Amendment resolution
value.excerpt: "Everybody to a 'T' thought it was totally appropriate," Trump said as lawmakers prepared a resolution calling for his removal from office.

value.title: Miranda Devine: Dems 'hatred' for Trump supporters is 'un-American'
value.excerpt: Fox News contributor Miranda Devine said Tuesday the rhetoric used against President Trump's supporters after the Capitol riots are dividing the country further.

value.title: Chicago Man Who Threatened to 'Kill' Democrats, Prevent Biden From Entering White House Arrested
value.excerpt: Louis Capriotti, a 45-year-old man from Chicago, made the alleged threats in a voicemail to a representative from New Jersey.

value.title: Trump's top bankers Deutsche Banks and Signature cut future ties
value.excerpt: In the wake of the deadly riots on Capitol Hill last week, Deutsche Bank and Signature Bank have said they are cutting future ties with President Donald Trump. That could leave the president personally on the hook for millions of dollars when several large loans he has personally guaranteed come due in the next two years.

value.title: Watch Rep. Torres' emotional plea to Mike Pence
value.excerpt: Rep. Norma Torres (D-CA) makes an emotional plea to Vice President Mike Pence during a House debate on a bill which would call for President Trump to be removed by the 25th Amendment.

value.title: Bette Midler Says Donald Trump Will 'Burn Down' The White House Before He Leaves
value.excerpt: "How many more will die in the service of this mediocrity? And watch, he'll burn the WH down before he goes," Midler tweeted Tuesday.

value.title: Easy for Joe Biden to 'heal' country with opposition silenced on social media: Dave Rubin
value.excerpt: Big Tech censorship of President Trump and conservatives needs to be addressed now, or soon everyone will be silenced, Dave Rubin warned Tuesday.

value.title: Forbes op-ed warns companies about hiring 'fabulists' from Trump administration
value.excerpt: Canceling anyone who was associated with Trump is not going to unite the country, Kelsey Bolar responded

value.title: Trump dropped by biggest lender Deutsche Bank for future business: NYT
value.excerpt: Deutsche Bank will not do business in the future with U.S. President Donald Trump or his companies in the wake of his supporters' assault on the U.S. Capitol, the New York Times reported.

value.title: Biden OMB nominee Neera Tanden received $731G salary from liberal nonprofit
value.excerpt: One of President-elect Biden's top Cabinet appointees earned more than $700,000 as the head of a leading liberal nonprofit, her financial disclosures reveal.

value.title: Trump acknowledged he bears some blame for Capitol riot in conversation with McCarthy: sources
value.excerpt: President Trump acknowledged that he bears some blame for the Capitol riot last week during a conversation with House Republican Leader Kevin McCarthy, a source familiar told Fox News.

value.title: Manchin calls second Trump impeachment bid 'ill-advised': 'Let the judicial system do its job'
value.excerpt: House Democrats' attempt to impeach President Trump for a second time in connection with last week's riot at the U.S. Capitol is "so ill-advised," Sen. Joe Manchin, D-W.Va. told "Special Report" Monday.

value.title: Critics mock NY Gov. Cuomo's sudden denunciation of lockdowns, suggest Trump hacked his Twitter account
value.excerpt: Democratic New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo raised eyebrows on Monday for his drastic shift on lockdowns during the pandemic.

value.title: Biden chooses veteran diplomat William Burns as his CIA director
value.excerpt: William Burns, chosen by Biden to head the CIA, built a 33-year career at the State Department under both Republican and Democratic presidents.

value.title: Pamela Anderson appeals Trump to pardon Assange and stand up for free speech
value.excerpt: EXCLUSIVE: Supporters of WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange are making a final appeal to the outgoing President Trump to show his commitment to free speech by granting a full pardon to the jailed publisher.
